data.title: Electron js
data.excerpt: Electron is a free and open-source software framework developed and maintained by GitHub. It allows for the development of desktop GUI applications using web technologies: it combines the Chromium rendering engine and the Node.js runtime. It was originally built for Atom.

data.title: Nextauth
data.excerpt: NextAuth.js is a complete open-source authentication solution for Next.js applications. It is designed from the ground up to support Next.js
